Alamun cutar COVID-19 na iya zama masu rikitarwa kuma waɗanda ke da cutar ba sa nuna alamun cutar.
Alamun da suka fi yawa sune zazzabin cizon sauro (88%) da kuma tari (68%).
Alamun da ba safai ba sun haɗa da rashin jin daɗi, yawan hawaye, rashin ƙamshi, rashin numfashi, ciwon tsoka, ciwon wuya, ciwon kai, jin iska/tsoro, amai, hawan jini (hemoptysis), ciwon jini, ko kuma cyanosis. WHO ta ce mutum ɗaya cikin shida yana rashin lafiya na dindindin kuma yana da wahalar numfashi.
Cibiyoyin Kula da Cututtuka na Amurka (CDC) sun ba da alamun farko kamar su numfashi mai tsanani, ciwon kirji, rashin jin daɗi, wahalar motsi, da kuma fuska ko lebe; ana buƙatar kulawa da gaggawa idan mutum ya sami alamun. Ciwon da ke ci gaba zai iya haifar da mummunan rauni, mutuwa ta hanyar numfashi mai tsanani (acute respiratory distress syndrome), sepsis, septic shock da sauransu.
Wasu marasa lafiya na iya zama marasa alamun cutar, amma idan an tabbatar da cutar, to masu bincike sun ba da shawarar cewa duk wanda ya sadu da waɗanda suka tabbatar da cutar ya kamata a kula da su sosai.
Kimanin kasar Sin na yawan alamun cutar ya kai kashi 44 cikin dari.
Lokacin bayyanar cututtuka (lokacin daga kamuwa da kwayar cutar zuwa bayyanar cututtuka) yawanci daga kwana ɗaya zuwa kwanaki 14; yawanci kwanaki biyar.
Har ila, ba a san yadda cututtuka suke yaɗuwa ba.
Ana zaton cewa cutar tana yaduwa ne a tsakanin mutanen da suka yi hulɗa da masu cutar tare da shan ruwan da ake yadawa ta hanyar tari, ɗagawa, ko magana; kuma wannan hulɗa tana tsakanin 1 zuwa 2 mita (3 zuwa 6 feet).
